
[1]tergiversation

   TERGIVERSA'TION, n. A shifting; shift; subterfuge; evasion.

   Writing is to be preferred before verbal conferences, as being more
   free from passion and tergiversation.

   1. Change; fickleness of conduct.

   The colonel, after all his tergiversation, lost his life in the king's
   service.
